{"https://github.com/Zettlr/Zettlr/commit/1d398f80b0076f33189a5d6f53b2772c150e6102": {"commit_message": "[Fix] Footnote refactor fixes (#5977)", "push_date": null, "ranked_scenarios": [{"id": "https://github.com/Zettlr/Zettlr/pull/5976", "summary": "[Refactor] Footnote parsing and rendering", "description": {"text": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for opening up this pull request! Please read this comment carefully\r\n  and make sure to fill in as much info as possible below as well.\r\n\r\n  First, the obligatory checklist. You must make sure to follow this list as\r\n  much as possible to make merging your PR as easy as possible:\r\n\r\n  1. I documented all behaviour within the code as far as I could.\r\n  2. This PR targets the develop branch and *not* the master branch.\r\n  3. I have tested my changes extensively and paid extra attention to potential\r\n     cross-platform issues (e./g. Cmd/Ctrl/Super key bindings)\r\n  4. I ran the `yarn lint` and `yarn test` commands successfully\r\n  5. I have added an entry to the CHANGELOG.md\r\n  6. I matched my code-style to the repository as far as possible\r\n  7. I agree that my code will be published under the GNUP GPL v3 license\r\n  8. In case I created new files, I added a header to them (see the existing\r\n     files for examples)\r\n  9. Before opening this PR, I ran `git pull` a last time to prevent any merge\r\n     issues\r\n\r\n  If you don't know how to fulfill some of the above points, feel free to open\r\n  your PR nevertheless and mention those points where you are unsure. The more\r\n  you can fulfill, the faster we can merge your PR, otherwise it will just take\r\n  longer.\r\n -->\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n<!-- Below, please describe what the PR does in one or two short sentences. -->\r\nThis PR refactors the footnote parsing and rendering.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n<!-- What changes did you make? Please explicitly state any breaking API changes so that nobody is confused why other components suddenly stop working -->\r\nThe footnote parser was refactored to use delimiters. The footnote reference parser was refactored to use a composite block parsing, which allows interior block nodes.\r\n\r\nThe footnote rendering was moved to a dedicated renderer rather than a CSS style. This enables nested nodes to be styled. I tried to use a class/theme based approach, but I don't think the class values are applied to child nodes, so this hard-coded style is the only way to get the styling to apply to the interior nodes.\r\n\r\nThe print page CSS was updated to add more styling to footnote reference body text.\r\n\r\n## Additional information\r\n<!-- If there is anything else that might be of interest, please provide it here -->\r\n\r\nImages:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1330\" height=\"909\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-10-29 at 06 29 58\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/99bb8936-491c-4bd5-907e-3a5f14e38f65\" />\r\n<img width=\"570\" height=\"446\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-10-29 at 06 42 24\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1edbe732-32bc-4c7e-b4e8-13345864c3a2\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- Please provide any testing system -->\r\nTested on: <!-- OS including version --> macOS 26\r\n"}, "closed_issues": [], "merged_at": null, "merge_commits": [], "RANK": 1, "COUNT": 2}]}}